nodes.bodyText:
@DanHeidinga The OJDK implementation generates adapter method (memberName) to invoke a method handle.
If we want to use similar trick as current OpenJ9 impl, then we need to find a way to generate a MN that points to a method which accepts vararg input and throw last argument (ie. we place the exception object in the appendix slot).
We will have to investigate how to create such memberName in java.
@babsingh do you have further insight on this?

